<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><Statute lims:pit-date="2012-06-28" lims:lastAmendedDate="2012-06-28" lims:current-date="2025-07-24" lims:inforce-start-date="2012-06-28" lims:fid="410297" lims:id="410297" bill-origin="commons" bill-type="govt-public" xml:lang="en" in-force="yes" xmlns:lims="http://justice.gc.ca/lims"><Identification lims:inforce-start-date="2012-06-28" lims:fid="410298" lims:id="410298"><BillNumber>C-278</BillNumber><Parliament><Session>1</Session><Number>41</Number><RegnalYear><Year-s>60-61</Year-s><Monarch>Elizabeth II</Monarch></RegnalYear><Year-s>2011-2012</Year-s></Parliament><LongTitle lims:inforce-start-date="2012-06-28" lims:fid="410299" lims:id="410299">An Act respecting a day to increase public awareness about epilepsy</LongTitle><ShortTitle lims:inforce-start-date="2012-06-28" lims:fid="410300" lims:id="410300" status="official">Purple Day Act</ShortTitle><RunningHead lims:inforce-start-date="2012-06-28" lims:fid="410301" lims:id="410301">Purple Day</RunningHead><BillHistory lims:inforce-start-date="2012-06-28" lims:fid="410302" lims:id="410302"><Stages lims:inforce-start-date="2012-06-28" stage="consolidation"><Date><YYYY>2025</YYYY><MM>7</MM><DD>25</DD></Date></Stages><Stages lims:inforce-start-date="2012-06-28" lims:fid="410304" lims:id="410304" stage="assented-to"><Date><YYYY>2012</YYYY><MM>6</MM><DD>28</DD></Date></Stages></BillHistory><Chapter lims:inforce-start-date="2012-06-28" lims:fid="410305" lims:id="410305"><ConsolidatedNumber official="no">P-38.8</ConsolidatedNumber><AnnualStatuteId><AnnualStatuteNumber>13</AnnualStatuteNumber><YYYY>2012</YYYY></AnnualStatuteId></Chapter><BillRefNumber date-time="2008-04-28">411329</BillRefNumber></Identification><Introduction lims:inforce-start-date="2012-06-28" lims:fid="410306" lims:id="410306"><Preamble lims:inforce-start-date="2012-06-28" lims:fid="410307" lims:id="410307" salutation="no"><Provision lims:inforce-start-date="2012-06-28" lims:fid="410308" lims:id="410308" format-ref="indent-0-0" language-align="yes" list-item="no"><MarginalNote lims:inforce-start-date="2012-06-28" lims:fid="410309" lims:id="410309">Preamble</MarginalNote><Text>Whereas the Parliament of Canada wishes to assist in efforts to educate and increase awareness, among members of the public, about people living with epilepsy;</Text></Provision></Preamble><Enacts lims:inforce-start-date="2012-06-28" lims:fid="410310" lims:id="410310"><Provision lims:inforce-start-date="2012-06-28" lims:fid="410311" lims:id="410311" format-ref="indent-0-0" language-align="yes" list-item="no"><Text>Now, therefore, Her Majesty, by and with the advice and consent of the Senate and House of Commons of Canada, enacts as follows:</Text></Provision></Enacts></Introduction><Body lims:inforce-start-date="2012-06-28" lims:fid="410312" lims:id="410312"><Heading lims:inforce-start-date="2012-06-28" lims:fid="410313" lims:id="410313" level="1"><TitleText>Short Title</TitleText></Heading><Section lims:inforce-start-date="2012-06-28" lims:lastAmendedDate="2012-06-28" lims:fid="410314" lims:id="410314"><MarginalNote lims:inforce-start-date="2012-06-28" lims:fid="410315" lims:id="410315">Short title</MarginalNote><Label>1</Label><Text>This Act may be cited as the <XRefExternal reference-type="act" link="P-38.8">Purple Day Act</XRefExternal>.</Text></Section><Heading lims:inforce-start-date="2012-06-28" lims:fid="410316" lims:id="410316" level="1"><TitleText>Purple Day</TitleText></Heading><Section lims:inforce-start-date="2012-06-28" lims:lastAmendedDate="2012-06-28" lims:fid="410317" lims:id="410317"><MarginalNote lims:inforce-start-date="2012-06-28" lims:fid="410318" lims:id="410318">Purple Day</MarginalNote><Label>2</Label><Text>Throughout Canada, in each and every year, the 26th day of March is to be known as “Purple Day”.</Text></Section><Section lims:inforce-start-date="2012-06-28" lims:lastAmendedDate="2012-06-28" lims:fid="410319" lims:id="410319"><MarginalNote lims:inforce-start-date="2012-06-28" lims:fid="410320" lims:id="410320">Wearing purple</MarginalNote><Label>3</Label><Text>On the 26th day of March, people are encouraged to wear the colour purple to indicate their support for people with epilepsy and to increase public awareness of this disorder.</Text></Section><Section lims:inforce-start-date="2012-06-28" lims:lastAmendedDate="2012-06-28" lims:fid="410321" lims:id="410321"><MarginalNote lims:inforce-start-date="2012-06-28" lims:fid="410322" lims:id="410322">Not a legal holiday</MarginalNote><Label>4</Label><Text>For greater certainty, Purple Day is not a legal holiday or a non-juridical day.</Text></Section></Body></Statute>